                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="anderson_sng_3"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">(1902-93) a US singer. In 1939 she was prevented from entering a hall to give a concert by the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/daughters-of-the-american-revolution" title="Daughters of the American Revolution definition"><span class="ndv">Daughters of the American Revolution</span></a> because she was black, so she gave a free concert from the steps of the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-lincoln-memorial#the_lincoln_memorial_topg_1" title="Lincoln Memorial definition"><span class="ndv">Lincoln Memorial</span></a>. In 1955, she became the first black singer to perform at the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-metropolitan-opera#the_metropolitan_opera_topg_1" title="Metropolitan Opera definition"><span class="ndv">Metropolitan Opera</span></a> in New York.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
